description.en-US: Technology offers the potential to for you as a patient to perform the exercises in your home and for the therapist to monitor the progress, adjusting the settings in the programme as required.  With support and advice alongside the use of technology a patients physiotherapy programme caters for all their needs.

Do you have a rehabilitation need?  Is accessing physiotherapy away from home challenging due to the current climate, travel or work commitments?  Then exercising at home is the solution.  Fully supported by a specialist and registered physiotherapist.

Physiotherapy at home using [Mira Rehab][1]![Mira](//images.ctfassets.net/j2xr2f1tr781/2lnzV64wHA31XRGZyoOdtp/1e8c1ac95b0d4bbfcc268866c9e5be1b/miraLogoWithMotto.png)
MIRA is a digital platform that uses motion tracking sensors to gamify physiotherapy exercises.

__MORE INFORMATION OR EXPANDING LINK FOR THE REST OF THIS INFO__

The results of your therapeutic 'gameplay' are analysed by a physiotherapist who then adjusts the levels and games according to your need - making your session easier or more difficult with the goal of progressing to more challenging exercises as you improve. 

Ongoing physiotherapy support via email, text or video conferencing is available alongside the interactive therapeutic gaming to ensure that all your needs are being met.

Pay once a month for daily home access to online interactive physiotherapy exercises, guidance and support. 

All for the price of a 30min face to face physiotherapy session.


[1]: http://www.mirarehab.com/ "MiraRehab"

description.en-US:
Are you a health professional who has clients who would benefit or enjoy using technology as part of their programme but not sure what is available?  The contact us for assistance - we can help.

Are you a client who would like to use technology to help with your rehabilitation? Contact us for information and advice as to what is available to assist.

__-----
The rest can be pasted in to a link regarding further information about the above???__ __I can then expand on the support I can offer in this area.__

Physiotherapy advice and support is offered for therapeutic gaming (Using MIRA Rehab) or through off the shelf consoles such as Nintendo Switch/Wii and Xbox Kinect gaming.  

Advice regarding other systems and approaches is also offered to either Health Professionals or private clients. Assistance and advice is available to find what suits individuals most appropriately to achieve the best rehabilitation results. 

Contact me for more information regarding either of the above services.

strapLine.en-US: Specialist knowledge and training on how to integrate technology in to all aspects of your physiotherapy practices.

description.en-US: Rebecca is a hard working and knowledgeable physiotherapist who strives to make therap fun and engaging.  She has a wealth of knowledge regarding technology and can apply many different games - both bespoke and off the shelf - to benefit the patients specific needs.

I am a physiotherapist with an interested and developed speciality in the use of technology as part of therapy.  Technology is already an integrated part of most of our lives and the innovation of technology within physiotherapy is no exception. 
With 20+ years of physiotherapy expereince I have spent the last 15 years researching and applying technology into my practice.  As the years have progressed, the technology has rapidly advanced in its sensitivity to movement and in how pateints can interact with it. There are numerous fantastic options  to make physical rehabilitation for a vast array of conditions fun, enjoyable and engaging.  Conditions range from brain injury to sprained ankle ligaments with most ailments that benefit from physiotherapy also benefiting from the interactive technology approach.

Success in your rehabilitation is the ultimate goal and Interactive Physio will assist you with any issues or queries you may have.  The beauty of technology and therapeutic gaming is that the options are endless for rehabilitation and you dont need to leave your sitting room to benefit from it.

If you want your physical rehabilitation to be more fun, then try active gaming.  Physiotherapy has used active gaming for over 15 years with an abundance of research to support its practice.  Using off the shelf gaming consoles can provide the platform from which clients can improve their balance, cardiovascular fitness, reaction speed, movement control, dexterity and enjoy the rehabilitation - which is recognised as a key component to successful progress.  Contact us for more information as to how we can help.

strapLine.en-US: Physiotherapy has used active gaming for over 15 years with an abundance of research to support its practice. Re-motivate your rehabiliation using cutting edge gaming technology from your home.

ans.en-US: Games are fun but the software has been designed to require specific movements and when used with a physiotherapists support these can promote rehab from the comfort of your own home. Research has demonstrated that games help motivate activity, which is a key element in rehabilitation. The software allows the physiotherapist to be specific with which movements are being targeted and worked on.

question.en-US: Is there any research or evidence to show that this approach works?

ans.en-US: Yes, there are many research papers now that provide evidence that the camera tracks movement accurately and that games that use the camera promote activity and boost health. Areas of research include Stroke, Parkinsons, MS, Cerebral Palsy, Acquired Brain Injury, Hemiplegia, Balance retraining.

question.en-US: What if I cant do the exercises?

ans.en-US: If you are unable to do the exercises that the games require then a simple consultation with the physiotherapist will help adjust the level of the required movement. This makes the games easier and therefore more achievable. However, following an initial assessment via video consultation this should not happen as the games will be set up specifically for your needs and ability.

question.en-US: What if the software or camera doesnt work?

ans.en-US: If the software or camera doesnt work then we offer technical support over the phone or via video consultation. Technology can be tricky at times but is easily resolved with some guidance. All instructions given on the outset are clear and straightforward to help avoid issues. Assistance is available if required.

question.en-US: What if I dont like the games or program?

ans.en-US: If you find that you dont enjoy or like the program then contact us and we can either offer a different gaming set of exercises or offer more traditional physiotherapy options to you, depending upon your need.

Calibration is the process in the program where the camera is looking for you and your limbs. If you are in a wheelchair the settings with reflect this and the camera will adjust accordingly. If space is limited then the calibration can be skipped all together, with only minimal impact on the sensitivity of the exercises and games.

description.en-US: Interactive Physio is a motivating way to approach your rehabilitative physical recovery. Using a combination of traditional physiotherapy alongside technology to make rehabilitation fun, engaging and interactively and all from your own home. Here is our team:

Interactive Physio is a new concept, combining traditional Physio approaches with technology, as both a method of communication AND treatment. 

If it's something you havent come across before, you probably will have questions about how it works, so we've answered some FAQs to help.
FAQs to help understand what Interactive Physio offers and how it can work
The interactive physio combines traditional Physiotherapy treatment with cutting edge technologies to provide a fun and motivating path to recovery.

Interactive Physio offers a selection of rehabilitation services and treatments and will cater them to your requirements depending on your specific need. 

Please see below for a description of each of these services.
We would love to hear from you, if its an enquiry or some feedback, please use the form below!
